 "coaching": {
  "headline": "This wasn't unlucky — it was lost in champ select: five losing lanes on paper, four of five players off their optimal role, and zero anti-heal into a Crunch. A 20-minute, -22 VP loss is the scoreboard agreeing.",
  "team": "Your own squad report names the optimal lineup — Willy support, Xeebs jungle, Cuban offlane, Mr_Meat carry, Goldilocks mid. This game you ran Willy jungle, Xeebs offlane, Cuban mid, Goldilocks support — four of five off-role, and the sim graded all five lanes 'theirs all game.' You then brought no anti-heal into Crunch (a healing bruiser) and lost the objective war 0 to 3 (they did 31.7k objective damage to your 81). There is no build or mechanical fix for this game; it's a drafting and role-discipline loss. Queue the assignment your own report computed and at minimum contest a single lane in the draft.",
  "whatShiftedIt": "Follow your computed lineup and don't first-pick into five bad lanes. If even two of you (Goldilocks to mid, Cuban to offlane) had been on-role with a favorable matchup, this is a different game. The anti-heal was the cherry on top — mandatory into Crunch, absent.",
  "perPlayer": {
   "a0c393cc-1437-4bdc-8168-64676ce2166c": "Forced onto Lt. Belica mid (0/4/0) when your assigned role is offlane — a carry main playing mid into Gideon is a coin flip you lost. This isn't your mechanics; it's the lineup. Play offlane where the report puts you.",
   "16f28434-561f-4f23-9454-40321f4a1ef3": "Muriel support, 1/5/2, 9 games of experience — you're a carry/mid forced into a support you don't know, into a losing matchup. Five deaths on an enchanter means you were caught out of position all game. Get back to mid.",
   "10edbf65-457d-48d0-9151-9df5b4fcb40a": "As the shot-caller this is your game to own: Yin jungle 0/2/2, perf 60 (62 below your average), off your support role. You set the draft and the lineup — both were wrong here. Lead the role assignment, not just the calls.",
